1355–1402":"1355–1402","1353–1382":"1353–1382","1378–1442":"1378–1442","1380–Male":"1380–Deceased","1382–Male":"1382–Deceased","about 1382":"about 1382","1402":"1402","about 1380":"about 1380","Abt 1377":"about 1377","1378":"1378","1355":"1355","1442":"1442","1353":"1353","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","Salwick, Lancashire, England":"Salwick, Lancashire, England","Salwick, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Salwick, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","Shrewsbury, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Shrewsbury, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Fenwick","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (northern) and Scottish: habitational name from either of two places in Northumberland or from one in Yorkshire, all of which are so named from Old English <i>fenn</i> ‘marsh, fen’ + <i>wīc</i> ‘outlying dairy farm’. There is also a place in Ayrshire, Scotland, which has the same name and origin. This last is the source of at least some early examples of the surname: Nicholaus Fynwyk was provost of Ayr in 1313, and Reginald de Fynwyk or Fynvyk appears as bailie and alderman of the same burgh in 1387 and 1401. The name is usually pronounced ‘Fennick’.","History: The name was brought over from England by several forebears, including George Fenwick (1603–56/7), a colonist from Brinkburn, Northumberland. He was one of the group of lords and gentlemen to whom the earl of Warwick, president of the Council for New England, granted forty leagues of territory west of the Narragansett River. George took up residence with his family at Saybrook, CT, in 1639. John Fenwick of Bynfield, Berkshire, England, established himself at Salem, NJ, in June 1675, the first Quaker settlement on the Delaware."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Anne","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of   Ann   or   Anne ."],"variants":[{"name":"Anni","meanings":["Pet form of   Ann   or   Anne ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Anne Fenwick was born in 1355, in Salwick, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom. She married Sir Robert de Clifton about 1377. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. She died in 1402, at the age of 47."},"et":{"1355–1402":"1355–1402","1353–1382":"1353–1382","1378–1442":"1378–1442","1380–Male":"1380–Surnud","1382–Male":"1382–Surnud","about 1382":"umbes 1382","1402":"1402","about 1380":"umbes 1380","Abt 1377":"umbes 1377","1378":"1378","1355":"1355","1442":"1442","1353":"1353","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","Salwick, Lancashire, England":"Salwick, Lancashire, England","Salwick, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Salwick, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Shrewsbury, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Shrewsbury, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1355–1402":"1355–1402","1353–1382":"1353–1382","1378–1442":"1378–1442","1380–Male":"1380–Kuollut","1382–Male":"1382–Kuollut","about 1382":"noin 1382","1402":"1402","about 1380":"noin 1380","Abt 1377":"noin 1377","1378":"1378","1355":"1355","1442":"1442","1353":"1353","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","Salwick, Lancashire, England":"Salwick, Lancashire, England","Salwick, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Salwick, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Shrewsbury, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Shrewsbury, Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1355–1402":"1355–1402","1353–1382":"1353–1382","1378–1442":"1378–1442","1380–Male":"1380–Décédé","1382–Male":"1382–Décédé","about 1382":"environ 1382","1402":"1402","about 1380":"environ 1380","Abt 1377":"environ 1377","1378":"1378","1355":"1355","1442":"1442","1353":"1353","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","Salwick, Lancashire, England":"Salwick, Lancashire, Angleterre","Salwick, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Salwick, Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Shrewsbury, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Shrewsbury, Shropshire, Angleterre, Roy